I just had the best, tastiest mouth watering, scrumptious donut ever. I stood there in the shop and ate this cream cheese, cream filled donut and didn't waste one crumb. Then I told all the people in the shop to buy one before someone else gets it. Absolutely insane I wanted to go back in the middle of the day and buy another one. This donut was oozing cream and I was scared that it would drop on the floor. I made sure that it didn't. It was soft, too soft and too fresh. If you are going to gain calories at least make sure that you are going to eat something that you cannot resist. My diet just went out the window

COVID INFESTED location!!! Stay away from this place. No one here wears a mask, gloves, uses sanitizers, or even tries to pretend to do so. When the number of cases goes back up in ny, this place would the perfect example of why that will happen. Of all the food places that has reopened, this is the first one where everyone has so much disregard for what, unfortunately for now, constitutes a social norm. There were five people working there, and they all laughed at me for bringing up this issue of them all not wearing masks, or using sanitary measures. Although, before the whole pandemic thing, this place has already been dirty, so I guess, what do you expect?
